Download & Install git on your system from https://git-scm.com/downloads.
After installing, set your username & email using these commands:
  git config --global user.name "your user name"
  git config --global user.email "your email"
To confirm changes, use:
  git config --list
Then quit using:
  exit

Next create account on https://github.com
Go to your profile by clicking at top right hand corner to edit or add additional info.
Create a new repository by clicking NEW (+) button at upper right corner.
Enter repository name, choose public or private and choose Initialize with READ ME. Click Create Repository button.

Create a local copy on the Git Bash
Create a Dir on the local system where you will store the copy of the repository.
  mkdir ~/your repository (created on the github.com)
  cd ~/your repository

Initialize it:
  git init

Then point the local repository to the remote repository (github.com)
  git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/yourrepository.git


In order to Fork a another user's repository:
Clone the repository using:
  git clone https://github.com/yourusername/repositoryname.git
